@page "/templates"
@inject ProductBranding Branding

<PageTitle>Excel Templates for Reporting, Forecasting, and Operations - @Branding.SiteName</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Preview ExcelToolStack templates for reporting, forecasting, operations, model review, and AI-ready spreadsheet workflows." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="@($"{Branding.SiteUrl}/templates")" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="@($"Excel templates for serious spreadsheet work - {Branding.SiteName}")" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="A curated template preview for reporting, forecasting, operations, and workbook quality control." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="directory-hero">
    <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Templates</p>
        <h1>Templates for serious spreadsheet work.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
            The template library is positioned around repeatable Excel work: reporting packs, trackers, model review,
            forecasting, and AI-ready prompts that help teams start with structure.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button button--primary" href="/templates/invoice-template-excel">Preview invoice template</a>
            <a class="button button--secondary" href="/tools">Explore planned tools</a>
            <a class="button button--secondary" href="/blog">Read template guides</a>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="template-preview-panel" aria-label="Template library preview">
        <div class="template-preview-panel__sheet">
            <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
            <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
            <span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span>
        </div>
        <strong>Reporting, finance, operations, QA</strong>
        <p>Reusable starting points for teams that need consistent workbook structure.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-shell section-shell--tight">
    <div class="template-grid page-grid excel-card-grid">
        <article class="workflow-directory-card">
            <span>Invoice</span>
            <h2>Excel invoice template</h2>
            <p>Public landing page for a clean invoice structure with line items, taxes, totals, notes, and payment terms.</p>
            <a href="/templates/invoice-template-excel">Preview invoice template</a>
        </article>
        <article class="workflow-directory-card">
            <span>Reporting</span>
            <h2>Monthly KPI reporting pack</h2>
            <p>Preview category for recurring dashboards, variance notes, and leadership-ready summaries.</p>
            <a href="/blog">Read reporting guides</a>
        </article>
        <article class="workflow-directory-card">
            <span>Forecasting</span>
            <h2>Forecast assumptions workbook</h2>
            <p>Planned templates for scenario planning, assumptions tracking, and cleaner model inputs.</p>
            <a href="/tools">View analysis tools</a>
        </article>
        <article class="workflow-directory-card">
            <span>Operations</span>
            <h2>Operations tracker kit</h2>
            <p>Structured surfaces for recurring trackers, reconciliations, task ownership, and status views.</p>
            <a href="/tools">View productivity tools</a>
        </article>
        <article class="workflow-directory-card">
            <span>Quality</span>
            <h2>Workbook review checklist</h2>
            <p>Reserved for model QA, formula review, handoff notes, and pre-presentation checks.</p>
            <a href="/blog">Read review guides</a>
        </article>
        <article class="workflow-directory-card">
            <span>AI prompts</span>
            <h2>AI spreadsheet prompt library</h2>
            <p>Future prompt patterns for explaining changes, summarizing tables, and creating analyst notes.</p>
            <a href="/">See AI workflow preview</a>
        </article>
        <article class="workflow-directory-card">
            <span>Launch</span>
            <h2>Template release preview</h2>
            <p>Public positioning only for now. No files are generated, uploaded, transformed, or processed.</p>
            <a href="/pricing">See pricing preview</a>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-shell section-shell--accent">
    <div class="section-heading section-heading--split">
        <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Template workflow</p>
            <h2>Start structured, then automate the repeatable parts.</h2>
            <p>Templates connect the ExcelToolStack tool pages into reporting, finance, and operations workflows.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="text-link" href="/ai-excel-formula-generator">Open Formula Copilot</a>
    </div>
    <div class="workflow-steps">
        <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Pick the workbook shape</h3>
            <p>Start from a reporting pack, tracker, invoice, or QA checklist instead of a blank workbook.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Clean and normalize inputs</h3>
            <p>Use cleanup and conversion workflows to prepare data before formulas, review, or handoff.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Document the logic</h3>
            <p>Add formula explanations, assumptions, and reviewer notes so teams can trust the workbook.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>
